IN RE: NOMINATION PETITION OF Kenneth WALKER, Jr. as DEMOCRATIC CANDIDATE FOR STATE REPRESENTATIVE FOR The 181ST LEGISLATIVE DISTRICT OBJECTION OF: Arthur GREEN AND Frances FOLK Appeal of: Kenneth Walker, Jr. No. 12 EAP 2018 Supreme Court of Pennsylvania. April 24, 2018 Adam J. Rodgers, for Kenneth Walker, Philadelphia, PA, Appellant. Adam Craig Bonin, The Law Office of Adam C. Bonin, Philadelphia, PA, for Frances Folk and Arthur Green, Appellees. City Commissioners of Philadelphia, Anthony Clark, Chairman, Philadelphia, PA, pro se. Kathleen Marie Kotula, Pennsylvania Department of State, Harrisburg, PA, for Department of State, Participants.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

AND NOW, this 24th day of April, 2018, as Appellant has failed to file a brief and reproduced record by the deadline imposed by this Court, and since he has offered no justification for this failure, the Motion to Quash Appeal is GRANTED.
